            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "if there really is no other way internally for Nvim to (already) know it was restarted, then to signal \"this is a restart\" without adding another `--foo` arg, we could use a dummy `'+:::'` arg. here's an old removed example of that: https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/64d55b74d83d566975e269bed0810d9008119ddf/src/nvim/ex_docmd.c#L4986-L4996",
            "commit_id": "732e382bd2bd2c7a4fd7f46787d977ab58fffa91",
